#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the volume level to use, as a percentage of full volume. Specify "
"-1 to use the default volume."
msgstr ""
"Določa raven glasnosti, ki se uporabi, kot odstotek polne glasnosti. "
"Navedite -1, če želite uporabiti privzeti zvezek."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4786
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<function>scheduleAudio()</function> is a &DBus; call to schedule the "
"specified audio file to be played at the specified date and time. Apart from "
"specifying a volume and omitting the message color and font parameters, its "
"usage is identical to <link linkend=\"scheduleMessage-descrip"
"\"><function>scheduleMessage</function></link> - see the description of that "
"function for further details."
msgstr ""
"<function>scheduleAudio()</function> je klic &DBus; za načrtovanje "
"predvajanja določene zvočne datoteke ob določenem datumu in času. Razen "
"določitve glasnosti in izpustitve parametrov barve sporočila in pisave je "
"njena uporaba enaka kot pri <link linkend=\"scheduleMessage-descrip"
"\"><function>scheduleMessage</function></link> - za več podrobnosti glejte "
"opis te funkcije."

#. Tag: refentrytitle
#: index.docbook:4797
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refentrytitle>edit</refentrytitle>"
msgstr "<refentrytitle>uredi</refentrytitle>"

#. Tag: refname
#: index.docbook:4800
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refname>edit</refname>"
msgstr "<refname>uredi</refname>"

#. Tag: refpurpose
#: index.docbook:4801
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Display the <link linkend=\"alarm-edit-dlg\">Alarm Edit dialog</link> to "
"edit an alarm."
msgstr ""
"Prikažite <link linkend=\"alarm-edit-dlg\">Pogovorno okno Uredi alarm</link> "
"za urejanje alarma."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: index.docbook:4805
#, no-c-format
msgid "bool edit(const QString&amp; <replaceable>eventID</replaceable>)"
msgstr "bool edit(const QString&amp; <replaceable>dogodekID</replaceable>)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the unique ID of the event to be edited, optionally prefixed by "
"the configuration name or numeric ID of the resource containing the event, "
"in the format <replaceable>[resourceID:]eventUID</replaceable>."
msgstr ""
"Določa edinstven ID dogodka, ki ga je treba urediti, po želji s predpono "
"namena konfiguracije ali številčnega ID vira, ki vsebuje dogodek, v obliki "
"<replaceable>[resourceID:]eventUID</replaceable>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:4823 index.docbook:4877 index.docbook:4909
#, no-c-format
msgid "Return value"
msgstr "Return value"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4824
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<returnvalue>false</returnvalue> if the specified alarm could not be found "
"or is read-only, <returnvalue>true</returnvalue> otherwise."
msgstr ""
"<returnvalue>false</returnvalue>, če določenega alarma ni bilo mogoče najti "
"ali je namenjen samo branju, <returnvalue>true</returnvalue> v nasprotnem "
"primeru."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4833
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<function>edit()</function> is a &DBus; call to display the <link linkend="
"\"alarm-edit-dlg\">Alarm Edit dialog</link> to edit the specified alarm."
msgstr ""
"<function>edit()</function> je klic &DBus; za prikaz <link linkend=\"alarm-"
"edit-dlg\">Pogovorno okno za urejanje alarma</link> za urejanje določenega "
"alarma."

#. Tag: refentrytitle
#: index.docbook:4842
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refentrytitle>editNew</refentrytitle>"
msgstr "<refentrytitle>editNew</refentrytitle>"

#. Tag: refname
#: index.docbook:4845
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refname>editNew</refname>"
msgstr "<refname>editNew</refname>"

#. Tag: refpurpose
#: index.docbook:4846
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Display the <link linkend=\"alarm-edit-dlg\">Alarm Edit dialog</link> to "
"edit a new alarm."
msgstr ""
"Prikažite <link linkend=\"alarm-edit-dlg\">Pogovorno okno Uredi alarm</link> "
"za urejanje novega alarma."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: index.docbook:4850
#, no-c-format
msgid "bool editNew(int <replaceable>type</replaceable>)"
msgstr "bool editNew(int <replaceable>tip</replaceable>)"

#. Tag: synopsis
#: index.docbook:4851
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"bool editNew(const QString&amp; <replaceable>templateName</replaceable>)"
msgstr ""
"bool editNew(const QString&amp; <replaceable>templateName</replaceable>)"

#. Tag: parameter
#: index.docbook:4857
#, no-c-format
msgid "type"
msgstr "vrsta"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4859
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the alarm type. The permissible values are DISPLAY, COMMAND, "
"EMAIL, AUDIO. These are defined in class <classname>KAlarmIface</classname> "
"in <filename>kalarmiface.h</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Določa vrsto alarma. Dovoljene vrednosti so DISPLAY, COMMAND, EMAIL, AUDIO. "
"Opredeljeni so v razredu <classname>KAlarmIface</classname> v "
"<filename>kalarmiface.h</filename>."

#. Tag: parameter
#: index.docbook:4867
#, no-c-format
msgid "templateName"
msgstr "imePredloge"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4869
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies the name of an alarm template to base the new alarm on."
msgstr "Določa ime predloge alarma, na kateri temelji nov alarm."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4878
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<returnvalue>false</returnvalue> if <parameter>type</parameter> has an "
"invalid value, or if no template with the name <parameter>templateName</"
"parameter> can be found; <returnvalue>true</returnvalue> otherwise."
msgstr ""
"<returnvalue>false</returnvalue>, če ima <parameter>vrsta</parameter> "
"neveljavno vrednost ali če ni mogoče najti nobene predloge z namenom "
"<parameter>templateName</parameter>; <returnvalue>true</returnvalue> sicer."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4888
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<function>editNew()</function> is a &DBus; call to display the <link linkend="
"\"alarm-edit-dlg\">Alarm Edit dialog</link> to edit a new alarm. If an alarm "
"type is specified as a parameter, a blank dialog is displayed. "
"Alternatively, if an alarm template name is specified as a parameter, the "
"dialog is preset with details from the template."
msgstr ""
"<function>editNew()</function> je klic &DBus; za prikaz <link linkend="
"\"alarm-edit-dlg\">Pogovorno okno za urejanje alarma</link> za urejanje "
"novega alarma. Če je kot parameter določena vrsta alarma, se prikaže prazno "
"pogovorno okno. Če je kot parameter navedeno ime predloge alarma, je "
"pogovorno okno prednastavljeno s podrobnostmi iz predloge."

#. Tag: refentrytitle
#: index.docbook:4899
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refentrytitle>list</refentrytitle>"
msgstr "<refentrytitle>list</refentrytitle>"

#. Tag: refname
#: index.docbook:4902
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refname>list</refname>"
msgstr "<refname>list</refname>"

#. Tag: refpurpose
#: index.docbook:4903
#, no-c-format
msgid "Return a list of scheduled alarms."
msgstr "Vračanje seznama načrtovanih alarmov."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: index.docbook:4906
#, no-c-format
msgid "QString list()"
msgstr "QString list()"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4910
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"List of alarms, separated by newlines, each in the format "
"<returnvalue><replaceable>resource_id</replaceable>:<replaceable>UID</"
"replaceable> <replaceable>time</replaceable> <replaceable>text</"
"replaceable></returnvalue>"
msgstr ""
"Seznam alarmov, ločenih z novimi vrsticami, vsak v obliki "
"<returnvalue><replaceable>resource_id</replaceable>:<replaceable>UID</"
"replaceable> <replaceable>čas</replaceable> <replaceable>besedilo</"
"replaceable></returnvalue>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4918
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<function>list()</function> is a &DBus; call to return a string containing a "
"summary of scheduled alarms. The list shows brief details of each pending "
"alarm: its resource identifier, UID, next scheduled time and message text or "
"file."
msgstr ""
"<function>list()</function> je klic &DBus; za vrnitev niza, ki vsebuje "
"povzetek načrtovanih alarmov. Na seznamu so prikazane kratke podrobnosti o "
"vsakem čakajočem alarmu: identifikator vira, UID, naslednji načrtovani čas "
"in besedilo sporočila ali datoteka."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:4929
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Line Interface"
msgstr "Vmesnik ukazne vrstice"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4931
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Command line options are provided to enable other programs to start up "
"&kalarm; if it is not already running, in order to trigger or cancel "
"scheduled alarms, or schedule new alarms. The reason for using command line "
"options for this purpose is that if &kalarm; were started without any "
"command line parameters and then sent &DBus; requests, it would start in its "
"default graphical mode, which is clearly undesirable for an inter-program "
"request."
msgstr ""
"Na voljo so možnosti ukazne vrstice, ki drugim programom omogočajo zagon "
"programa &kalarm;, če ta še ni zagnan, da sprožijo ali prekličejo načrtovane "
"alarme ali načrtujejo nove alarme. Razlog za uporabo možnosti ukazne vrstice "
"v ta namen je, da če bi se program &kalarm; zagnal brez parametrov ukazne "
"vrstice in nato pošiljal zahteve &DBus;, bi se zagnal v privzetem grafičnem "
"načinu, kar je za medprogramsko zahtevo očitno nezaželeno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4939
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Programs should first check whether &kalarm; is already running; if it is, "
"they should instead use &DBus; calls to request these operations."
msgstr ""
"Programi morajo najprej preveriti, ali je program &kalarm; že zagnan; če je, "
"morajo za zahtevo teh operacij namesto tega uporabiti klice &DBus;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4943
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The command line options for scheduling a new alarm are as described in the "
"chapter <link linkend=\"cmdline-operation\">Command Line Operation</link>. "
"The options for triggering and canceling scheduled alarms are as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Možnosti ukazne vrstice za načrtovanje novega alarma so opisane v poglavju "
"<link linkend=\"cmdline-operation\">Operacije ukazne vrstice</link>. "
"Možnosti za sprožitev in preklic načrtovanih alarmov so naslednje:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4948
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Normal users may also if they wish use these command line options (assuming "
"that they can supply the necessary parameter information)."
msgstr ""
"Če želijo, lahko te možnosti ukazne vrstice uporabijo tudi običajni "
"uporabniki (če lahko zagotovijo potrebne podatke o parametrih)."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:4962
#, no-c-format
msgid "--cancelEvent <replaceable>eventID</replaceable>"
msgstr "--cancelEvent <replaceable>eventID</replaceable>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:4963
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cancel the alarm with the specified event ID. The event ID is the unique ID "
"of the event, optionally prefixed by the ID of the resource containing the "
"event, in the format <replaceable>[resourceID:]eventUID</replaceable>. The "
"action taken is the same as for the <link linkend=\"cancelEvent"
"\">cancelEvent()</link> &DBus; call. <option>--triggerEvent</option> cannot "
"be specified with this option."
msgstr ""
"Prekliči alarm z navedenim ID dogodka. ID dogodka je edinstven ID dogodka, "
"po želji s predpono ID vira, ki vsebuje dogodek, v obliki "
"<replaceable>[resourceID:]eventUID</replaceable>. Izvedeno dejanje je enako "
"kot pri klicu <link linkend=\"cancelEvent\">cancelEvent()</link> &DBus;. "
"<option>--triggerEvent</option> s to možnostjo ni mogoče določiti."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:4973
#, no-c-format
msgid "--triggerEvent <replaceable>eventID</replaceable>"
msgstr "--triggerEvent <replaceable>eventID</replaceable>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:4974
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Trigger the alarm with the specified event ID. The event ID is the unique ID "
"of the event, optionally prefixed by the ID of the resource containing the "
"event, in the format <replaceable>[resourceID:]eventUID</replaceable>. The "
"action taken is the same as for the <link linkend=\"triggerEvent"
"\">triggerEvent()</link> &DBus; call. <option>--cancelEvent</option> cannot "
"be specified with this option."
msgstr ""
"Sprožite alarm z določenim ID dogodka. ID dogodka je edinstven ID dogodka, "
"po želji s predpono ID vira, ki vsebuje dogodek, v obliki "
"<replaceable>[resourceID:]eventUID</replaceable>. Izvedeno dejanje je enako "
"kot pri klicu <link linkend=\"triggerEvent\">triggerEvent()</link> &DBus;. "
"<option>--cancelEvent</option> s to možnostjo ni mogoče določiti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:4987
#, no-c-format
msgid "Examples are:"
msgstr "Primeri so:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:4989
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>kalarm</command> <option>--"
"triggerEvent <replaceable>&kalarm;-387486299.702</replaceable></option></"
"userinput>\n"
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>kalarm</command> <option>--"
"cancelEvent <replaceable>&kalarm;-388886299.793</replaceable></option></"
"userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>kalarm</command> <option>--"
"triggerEvent <replaceable>&kalarm;-387486299.702</replaceable></option></"
"userinput>\n"
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>kalarm</command> <option>--"
"cancelEvent <replaceable>&kalarm;-388886299.793</replaceable></option></"
"userinput>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:4997
#, no-c-format
msgid "Questions and Answers"
msgstr "Vprašanja in odgovori"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5002
#, no-c-format
msgid "What configuration files does &kalarm; use?"
msgstr "Katere konfiguracijske datoteke uporablja &kalarm;?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5005
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kalarm;'s configuration is held in the following files in the folder "
"<command>qtpaths --paths GenericConfigLocation</command> :"
msgstr ""
"konfiguracija &kalarm; je shranjena v naslednjih datotekah v mapi "
"<command>qtpaths --paths GenericConfigLocation</command> :"

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5010
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>kalarmrc</filename> holds your &kalarm; preferences."
msgstr "<filename>kalarmrc</filename> hrani vaše nastavitve &kalarm;."

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5015
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>kalarmresources</filename> holds the list of alarm calendars "
"currently used by &kalarm;."
msgstr ""
"<filename>kalarmresources</filename> vsebuje seznam koledarjev alarmov, ki "
"jih trenutno uporablja &kalarm;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5024
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where does &kalarm; store its alarms?"
msgstr "Kje &kalarm; shranjuje svoje alarme?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5028
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When &kalarm; is run the first time, it creates the following alarm "
"calendars in the folder <command>qtpaths --paths GenericDataLocation</"
"command> :"
msgstr ""
"Ko je &kalarm; prvič zagnan, ustvari naslednje koledarje alarmov v mapi "
"<command>qtpaths --paths GenericDataLocation</command>:"

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5034
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>kalarm/calendar.ics</filename>, which holds active alarms."
msgstr "<filename>kalarm/calendar.ics</filename>, ki vsebuje aktivne alarme."

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5039
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>kalarm/expired.ics</filename>, which holds archived alarms."
msgstr "<filename>kalarm/expired.ics</filename>, ki vsebuje arhivirane alarme."

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5044
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>kalarm/template.ics</filename>, which holds alarm templates."
msgstr "<filename>kalarm/template.ics</filename>, ki vsebuje predloge alarmov."

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5049
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>kalarm/displaying.ics</filename>, which is a special calendar file "
"to hold details of alarms currently being displayed, which allows &kalarm;, "
"when it is restarted, to redisplay alarms which were being displayed when it "
"last stopped."
msgstr ""
"<filename>kalarm/displaying.ics</filename>, ki je posebna koledarska "
"datoteka za podrobnosti o trenutno prikazanih alarmih, ki &kalarm;u ob "
"ponovnem zagonu omogoča, da znova prikaže alarme, ki so bili prikazani, ko "
"se je nazadnje zaustavil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5056
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can subsequently replace these calendars, except <filename>displaying."
"ics</filename>, or create additional alarm calendars in any location which "
"you choose. You can find out which calendar files are currently in use by "
"viewing each calendar's details in the alarm calendars list."
msgstr ""
"Te koledarje lahko naknadno zamenjate, razen <filename>displaying.ics</"
"filename>, ali ustvarite dodatne koledarje alarmov na kateri koli lokaciji, "
"ki jo izberete. Katere koledarske datoteke so trenutno v uporabi, lahko "
"ugotovite tako, da si ogledate podrobnosti vsakega koledarja na seznamu "
"alarmnih koledarjev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5066
#, no-c-format
msgid "What format are alarms stored in?"
msgstr "V kakšnem tipu datoteke so shranjeni alarmi?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5069
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The calendar files in which &kalarm; stores its alarms are text files whose "
"format is defined by the document <ulink url=\"http://www.w3.org/2002/12/cal/"
"rfc2445.html\">RFC2445 - Internet Calendaring and Scheduling Core Object "
"Specification (iCalendar)</ulink>. This is the standard format used by all "
"kdepim applications. &kalarm; uses certain non-standard properties, in "
"conformance with RFC2445. These are documented in the <filename>DESIGN-"
"kalarmcalendar.html</filename> file which is distributed with &kalarm;."
msgstr ""
"Koledarske datoteke, v katerih je &kalarm; shranjuje svoje alarme, so "
"besedilne datoteke, katerih tip je določen z dokumentom <ulink url=\"http://"
"www.w3.org/2002/12/cal/rfc2445.html\">RFC2445 - Specifikacija jedrnega "
"objekta internetnega koledarja in razporejanja (iCalendar )</ulink>. To je "
"standardni format, ki ga uporabljajo vse aplikacije kdepim. &kalarm; "
"uporablja določene nestandardne lastnosti v skladu z RFC2445. Ti so "
"dokumentirani v datoteki <filename>DESIGN-kalarmcalendar.html</filename>, ki "
"se distribuira skupaj z &kalarm;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5083
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is the function of &kalarm;'s Akonadi plugin?"
msgstr "Kakšna je funkcija &kalarm;ovega vtičnika Akonadi?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5086
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kalarm; uses its Akonadi plugin to provide all features which depend on "
"&akonadi; (the &kde; &PIM; cross-desktop storage service). If this plugin is "
"not installed and enabled, &kalarm; will lack the following features:"
msgstr ""
"&kalarm; uporablja svoj vtičnik Akonadi za zagotavljanje vseh funkcij, ki so "
"odvisne od &akonadi; (storitev za shranjevanje &kde; &PIM; med namizji). Če "
"ta vtičnik ni nameščen in omogočen, &kalarm; ne bo imel naslednjih funkcij:"

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5092
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sending emails via &kmail;, leaving &Sendmail; as the only option to send "
"emails (see <link linkend=\"preferences-email\">Email preferences</link>)."
msgstr ""
"Pošiljanje e-pošte prek &kmail;, zapustitev &Sendmail; kot edina možnost za "
"pošiljanje e-pošte (glejte <link linkend=\"preferences-email\">E-poštne "
"nastavitve</link>)."

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5097
#, no-c-format
msgid "Drag and drop of emails."
msgstr "Vlek in spuščanje e-pošte."

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5100
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selection of email addresses from &kaddressbook;."
msgstr "Izbira e-poštnih naslovov iz &kaddressbook;."

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5103
#, no-c-format
msgid "Import of birthdays from &kaddressbook;."
msgstr "Uvoz rojstnih dni iz &kaddressbook;."

#. Tag: simpara
#: index.docbook:5106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Migration of &akonadi; alarm calendar resources on the first run of a new "
"version of &kalarm;."
msgstr ""
"Selitev &akonadi; virov koledarja alarmov ob prvem zagonu nove različice "
"&kalarm;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the plugin is installed, it can be enabled or disabled in the <link "
"linkend=\"preferences-general\">General</link> tab of the Configuration "
"dialog."
msgstr ""
"Če je vtičnik nameščen, ga lahko omogočite ali onemogočite na zavihku <link "
"linkend=\"preferences-general\">Splošno</link> v pogovornem oknu za "
"konfiguracijo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5119
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is the program <application>kalarmautostart</application>?"
msgstr "Kaj je program <application>kalarmautostart</application>?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<application>kalarmautostart</application> is a little helper program whose "
"function is to autostart &kalarm; at login."
msgstr ""
"<application>kalarmautostart</application> je majhen pomožni program, "
"katerega funkcija je samodejni zagon &kalarm; ob prijavi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kalarm; is usually restored by the session manager at login (to redisplay "
"its windows in the same state as they were when you logged off). But if it "
"was not running when you logged off, it would not be started by the session "
"manager and therefore needs to be autostarted. The problem is that when an "
"application is both session managed and autostarted, there is no guarantee "
"as to which will occur first. If autostart gets in first, it will prevent "
"the session manager from restoring the application's state."
msgstr ""
"&kalarm; običajno obnovi upravljalnik seje ob prijavi (da znova prikaže "
"svoja okna v enakem stanju, kot so bila, ko ste se odjavili). Če pa se ne bi "
"izvajal, ko ste se odjavili, ga upravljalnik seje ne bi zagnal, zato ga je "
"treba samodejno zagnati. Težava je v tem, da ko je aplikacija upravljana "
"seja in se samodejno zažene, ni zagotovila, kaj se bo zgodilo prej. Če se "
"samodejno zažene prvi, bo upravitelju seje preprečil obnovitev stanja "
"aplikacije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To avoid this problem, <application>kalarmautostart</application> is "
"autostarted at login instead of &kalarm;. All it does is wait for a short "
"time (to ensure that the session manager has time to do its job) before "
"starting &kalarm;, at which point it terminates."
msgstr ""
"Da bi se izognili tej težavi, se <application>kalarmautostart</application> "
"samodejno zažene ob prijavi namesto &kalarm;. Vse, kar naredi, je, da počaka "
"kratek čas (da zagotovi, da ima upravitelj seje čas za opravljanje svojega "
"dela), preden zažene &kalarm;, na kateri točki se zaključi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5144
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I use &kalarm; on a non-&plasma; desktop?"
msgstr "Kako lahko uporabljam &kalarm; na napravi, ki ni &plasma; namizje?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To run &kalarm; on a non-&plasma; desktop, the main requirement is to ensure "
"that &kalarm; is run automatically whenever you log in. More detailed "
"instructions are contained in the <filename>INSTALL</filename> file which is "
"distributed with &kalarm;."
msgstr ""
"Za zagon &kalarm; na napravi, ki ni &plasma; namizju, je glavna zahteva "
"zagotoviti, da &kalarm; se samodejno zažene vsakič, ko se prijavite. "
"Podrobnejša navodila so v datoteki <filename>INSTALL</filename>, ki je "
"priložena &kalarm;."

